  "prompt": "I got placed in TCS's EIS stream in my campus placement. Will I get a job in EIS or in IT?",
  "response": "Congratulations on your placement in TCS's **Enterprise Intelligent Systems (EIS)** stream! The EIS stream is a specialized domain within TCS that focuses on **IT services, consulting, and solutions** tailored to enterprise needs, particularly in areas like **IoT (Internet of Things), AI/ML, industrial automation, and smart systems**.\n\n### Will you get a job in EIS or IT?\n\n1. **EIS is part of IT**:  \n   EIS is not separate from IT; it is a specialized domain within TCS's broader IT services. So, technically, you are being hired into an IT role, but with a focus on **enterprise systems and intelligent technologies**.\n\n2. **Your Role Will Likely Be in EIS**:  \n   Since you were placed in the EIS stream, your initial role will likely align with EIS projects. You may work on developing smart solutions, IoT platforms, data analytics, or automation tools for enterprise clients.\n\n3. **Flexibility in TCS**:  \n   TCS often provides opportunities for employees to switch domains or work on projects outside their initial stream based on business needs, skill sets, and preferences. So, while you start in EIS, there might be opportunities to explore other IT domains in the future.\n\n4. **Learning and Upskilling**:  \n   TCS emphasizes continuous learning and provides training programs. If you want to transition to a different IT domain later, you can upskill yourself accordingly.\n\n### Key Points:\n- You are joining TCS as an **IT professional** in the **EIS domain**.\n- Your initial projects will likely be related to EIS, but you may have opportunities to explore other IT areas in the future.\n- Focus on building your skills in EIS-related technologies (IoT, AI/ML, etc.) to excel in your role.\n\nIf you're passionate about intelligent systems and enterprise solutions, this is a great start to your career. Best of luck! \ud83d\ude80",
  "temperature": 1.0,
